						<summary>

						<p>This records a gift of 30 <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> of gold for burning a perpetual lamp in the temple under the name <hi rend="italic">Kumaramāttaṇḍan</hi>, by <hi rend="bold">Aḻiviṉ-Kaḷḷaraśi</hi> <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> <hi rend="bold">Śembiyaṉ Buvanigaṅgaraiyan.</hi> The donor has been taken as <hi rend="bold">the younger brother</hi> of the Western Gaṅga chief <hi rend="bold">Gaṅgamārttāṇḍaṉ</hi> <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> <hi rend="bold">Śembiyan Prithivigaṅgaraiyaṉ</hi> and son of <hi rend="bold">Rājāditya Mahādēva</hi> (<hi rend="italic">M.E.R.</hi> for 1931, Part II, para 8). This is an inscription of <hi rend="bold">Parāntaka I.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
